A
GUIDE
TO
THE
USE
OF
THE
M
I
T
CONE
TABLES
THE
SECOND
AND
THIRD
VOLUMES
OF
THE
MIT
CONE
TABLES
HAVE
BEEN
FOUND
TO
BE
UNSATISFACTORY
IN
TWO
RESPECTS
THEY
HAVE
BEEN
CRITICIZED
BECAUSE
OF
THEIR
INCONVENIENT
TABULATION
AND
BECAUSE
THE
THEORY
ON
WHICH
THEY
ARE
BASED
IS
INADEQUATE
NEAR
THE
CONE
SURFACE
THE
FORMER
IS
CLIMINATED
BY
MEANS
OF
A
COORDINATE
TRANSFORMATION
EMPIRICAL
EVIDENCE
IS
PRESENTED
TO
SHOW
THAT
THE
LATTER
MAY
BE
IGNORED
IN
PRACTICE
THE
EXACT
NATURE
OF
CERTAIN
NUMERICAL
ERRORS
IN
THE
TABLE
IS
ALSO
POINTED
OUT
